WEBVTT

1
00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:12.074
Watch Online Movies and Series for FREE
www.osdb.link/lm

2
00:00:26.050 --> 00:00:26.920
Jean!

3
00:00:28.300 --> 00:00:29.300
He's dead...

4
00:00:31.300 --> 00:00:33.680
I'm in my prime again today!

5
00:00:34.180 --> 00:00:37.307
This speed...
it's the Red Meteor Scarlet.

6
00:00:37.390 --> 00:00:39.310
THE RED METEOR. SCARLET

7
00:00:40.690 --> 00:00:42.897
O wind that sweeps through.

8
00:00:42.980 --> 00:00:45.647
become a tornado
and tear the enemy apart...

9
00:00:45.730 --> 00:00:47.777
This incantation...

10
00:00:47.860 --> 00:00:51.617
It is said that no one who has seen
those flames has ever survived...

11
00:00:51.700 --> 00:00:52.907
The Azure Grim Reaper!

12
00:00:52.990 --> 00:00:53.907
Blue Death!

13
00:00:53.990 --> 00:00:55.537
Blast forth.

14
00:00:55.620 --> 00:00:57.160
Tornado Blade!

15
00:00:59.410 --> 00:01:01.920
THE AZURE GRIM REAPER. BLUE DEATH

16
00:01:02.920 --> 00:01:04.546
Marja! Nadja!

17
00:01:04.629 --> 00:01:07.337
Dammit! They were targeting
our back line from the start!

18
00:01:07.420 --> 00:01:08.420
You bastards!

19
00:01:10.630 --> 00:01:11.680
What now?!

20
00:01:19.060 --> 00:01:20.107
Curse you!

21
00:01:20.190 --> 00:01:21.190
Gotcha!

22
00:01:21.630 --> 00:01:23.270
I can see through you!

23
00:01:24.570 --> 00:01:27.027
You were careless. You fool.

24
00:01:27.110 --> 00:01:28.407
THE LAUGHING GOLDEN SKULL.
GOLDSKULL

25
00:01:28.490 --> 00:01:30.640
THE HEAVY ARMOR OF MYSTIC MIST.
MAUVE TITAN

26
00:01:31.210 --> 00:01:32.740
We've come this far...

27
00:01:34.620 --> 00:01:38.250
Do you think you can escape from us?

28
00:01:40.330 --> 00:01:44.630
A-All those rare items that
I painstakingly collected...

29
00:01:47.710 --> 00:01:49.970
Notice. the battle is over.

30
00:03:18.300 --> 00:03:20.970
THAT TIME I GOT REINCARNATED
AS A SLIME SEASON 4

31
00:03:23.010 --> 00:03:24.977
EPISODE 76: INVITATION

32
00:03:25.060 --> 00:03:27.647
What a bunch of weaklings!
This is hardly challenging!

33
00:03:27.730 --> 00:03:29.437
You said it!

34
00:03:29.520 --> 00:03:32.197
We're invincible and the strongest.

35
00:03:32.280 --> 00:03:35.567
They are no match for us!

36
00:03:35.650 --> 00:03:39.947
Hey. don't get too cocky.
This is still part of the job. after all.

37
00:03:40.030 --> 00:03:41.407
Y-Yeah...

38
00:03:41.490 --> 00:03:43.327
We got it. of course.

39
00:03:43.410 --> 00:03:45.277
But I suppose...

40
00:03:45.360 --> 00:03:47.337
We can go for another round. can't we?

41
00:03:47.420 --> 00:03:48.920
Let's go!

42
00:03:56.830 --> 00:03:59.140
Since the incident with Team Green Fury.

43
00:03:59.640 --> 00:04:03.690
we've been hunting challengers. or rather.
undergoing special training every day.

44
00:04:05.020 --> 00:04:08.270
There's no guarantee that Green Fury
won't come back for revenge.

45
00:04:09.930 --> 00:04:14.460
The dungeon is operating smoothly.
and the town is bustling with activity.

46
00:04:15.820 --> 00:04:19.570
Masayuki is truly an excellent poster kid.

47
00:04:20.209 --> 00:04:22.497
As if he were the very
embodiment of pure luck.

48
00:04:22.580 --> 00:04:25.790
he completed a rare set
of equipment from the series.

49
00:04:26.580 --> 00:04:30.500
Taking advantage of the momentum.
they are now aiming for the 50th floor.

50
00:04:33.290 --> 00:04:35.037
Starting with Masayuki's team.

51
00:04:35.120 --> 00:04:39.257
we edited and aired montages
of challengers in the spotlight.

52
00:04:39.340 --> 00:04:42.180
and those seem to have
sparked their motivation.

53
00:04:44.600 --> 00:04:48.020
Among those seeking power and fame.

54
00:04:48.600 --> 00:04:52.110
the number of truly skilled
challengers has been growing...

55
00:04:52.970 --> 00:04:56.407
And standing tall before
all of them. is us four.

56
00:04:56.490 --> 00:04:57.607
Look!

57
00:04:57.690 --> 00:04:58.907
Here they come!

58
00:04:58.990 --> 00:05:01.990
The Dungeon Dominators!

59
00:05:05.680 --> 00:05:08.680
You can't have a game without
a proper challenge. after all.

60
00:05:08.910 --> 00:05:10.960
We absolutely aren't just playing around!

61
00:05:12.960 --> 00:05:15.337
It just doesn't quite hit the spot.

62
00:05:15.420 --> 00:05:18.137
Aren't there any tougher challengers?

63
00:05:18.220 --> 00:05:20.477
Easy. now.

64
00:05:20.560 --> 00:05:22.387
Once the dungeon's reputation spreads.

65
00:05:22.470 --> 00:05:25.137
more and more strong challengers
will start showing up.

66
00:05:25.220 --> 00:05:28.350
We gotta train harder
and get stronger!

67
00:05:30.350 --> 00:05:33.440
You've returned. Master Rimuru.

68
00:05:33.980 --> 00:05:38.567
You have a guest. and I was
just on my way to fetch you.

69
00:05:38.650 --> 00:05:40.700
Oh? A guest?

70
00:05:41.240 --> 00:05:43.530
I see that Lady Milim is with us as well.

71
00:05:44.030 --> 00:05:45.197
That's perfect.

72
00:05:45.280 --> 00:05:47.200
Why's that?

73
00:05:52.230 --> 00:05:54.917
Pardon the intrusion. Master Rimuru.

74
00:05:55.000 --> 00:05:55.657
Huh?!

75
00:05:55.740 --> 00:05:56.910
Frey!

76
00:05:58.130 --> 00:06:00.970
Um. what brings you here today?

77
00:06:01.550 --> 00:06:04.177
It's nothing of concern.

78
00:06:04.260 --> 00:06:05.847
Oh hi. Milim.

79
00:06:05.930 --> 00:06:07.500
So here you are.

80
00:06:08.680 --> 00:06:12.600
That reminds me.
about the homework I gave you...

81
00:06:12.970 --> 00:06:14.517
Have you finished it yet?

82
00:06:14.600 --> 00:06:18.527
This brat just ditched work
to come here and have some fun.

83
00:06:18.610 --> 00:06:22.740
Y-You're mistaken!
There's a very valid reason for this!

84
00:06:24.060 --> 00:06:25.070
I see.

85
00:06:26.410 --> 00:06:29.037
The guard I assigned to watch you
was wrapped up in a mat.

86
00:06:29.120 --> 00:06:30.667
and was groaning in pain...

87
00:06:30.750 --> 00:06:34.170
Surely you have a very valid
reason for that.

88
00:06:35.380 --> 00:06:38.387
I-I was... with Rimuru and the others...

89
00:06:38.470 --> 00:06:39.047
Huh?

90
00:06:39.130 --> 00:06:42.677
Silly you. You could've just
told us you were busy!

91
00:06:42.760 --> 00:06:45.597
Had I known that. I would not
have dragged you along. My bad.

92
00:06:45.680 --> 00:06:47.767
You should've told us.

93
00:06:47.850 --> 00:06:50.270
You meanies!

94
00:06:53.100 --> 00:06:55.187
It's not what you think. Frey!

95
00:06:55.270 --> 00:06:57.440
P-Please hear me out!

96
00:06:58.570 --> 00:07:01.320
Oh. I will. gladly.

97
00:07:03.240 --> 00:07:07.860
We'll do that. all day long.
once we get home.

98
00:07:14.160 --> 00:07:15.497
Phew...

99
00:07:15.580 --> 00:07:18.507
Somehow we averted it
without getting involved.

100
00:07:18.590 --> 00:07:20.917
That was some teamwork well done.

101
00:07:21.000 --> 00:07:22.587
Wasn't that the best ever?

102
00:07:22.670 --> 00:07:23.587
Right!

103
00:07:23.670 --> 00:07:25.927
Speaking of which. Master Rimuru.

104
00:07:26.010 --> 00:07:29.367
What and where have you
been up to until now?

105
00:07:29.450 --> 00:07:30.307
Huh?!

106
00:07:30.390 --> 00:07:33.597
W-Well. I was just researching. you know!

107
00:07:33.680 --> 00:07:37.567
I was researching the fighting styles
of the dungeon challengers firsthand!

108
00:07:37.650 --> 00:07:39.150
Firsthand?

109
00:07:39.810 --> 00:07:41.020
That means...

110
00:07:41.650 --> 00:07:44.947
You were having a blast
playing in the dungeon?

111
00:07:45.030 --> 00:07:47.450
S-She's so sharp!

112
00:07:48.280 --> 00:07:50.997
I shall devote myself
to studying magic in my room.

113
00:07:51.080 --> 00:07:53.997
I guess I'll tag along too.

114
00:07:54.080 --> 00:07:59.500
Sorry. Milim. It really pisses me off
when people do these dumb stunts on me.

115
00:07:59.790 --> 00:08:00.667
Notice.

116
00:08:00.750 --> 00:08:02.710
There's no need for excuses.

117
00:08:03.300 --> 00:08:05.927
If you act with conviction.
the problem will be solved.

118
00:08:06.010 --> 00:08:08.427
Huh? What do you mean?

119
00:08:08.510 --> 00:08:10.677
Master Rimuru!

120
00:08:10.760 --> 00:08:13.437
Here you are.

121
00:08:13.520 --> 00:08:14.437
Mjöllmile?!

122
00:08:14.520 --> 00:08:17.807
We have received a letter
from the Council.

123
00:08:17.890 --> 00:08:21.897
I'm guessing it's an invitation to attend
the meeting where they'll decide...

124
00:08:21.980 --> 00:08:24.317
...whether or not to accept us
into the Council.

125
00:08:24.400 --> 00:08:26.027
I see.

126
00:08:26.110 --> 00:08:28.577
I was expecting this anyway.

127
00:08:28.660 --> 00:08:30.787
What do you mean?

128
00:08:30.870 --> 00:08:36.287
I suspected the Green Fury was a scout
sent by the Council to investigate us.

129
00:08:36.370 --> 00:08:39.150
So. I did the same thing.

130
00:08:39.539 --> 00:08:43.336
Rather. it was Ms. Raphael who actually
took care of everything...

131
00:08:43.419 --> 00:08:45.087
...while we were out having fun.

132
00:08:45.170 --> 00:08:47.337
My apologies.

133
00:08:47.420 --> 00:08:51.347
I really thought you were just having fun
with Lady Milim and everyone.

134
00:08:51.430 --> 00:08:53.097
It's fine.

135
00:08:53.180 --> 00:08:55.430
Can't fault you
for perceiving it that way.

136
00:09:01.980 --> 00:09:04.387
I managed to smooth
things over just in time.

137
00:09:04.470 --> 00:09:07.527
But even with Ms. Raphael's help.

138
00:09:07.610 --> 00:09:11.367
it is a fact I got so caught up in playing
that I neglected everything else.

139
00:09:11.450 --> 00:09:13.870
I have to know when to stop.

140
00:09:14.650 --> 00:09:15.827
Wait.

141
00:09:15.910 --> 00:09:19.377
You were conducting the investigation
up until a moment ago. weren't you?

142
00:09:19.460 --> 00:09:20.587
Ah.

143
00:09:20.670 --> 00:09:25.460
Then. what were you investigating
after Green Fury left?

144
00:09:28.310 --> 00:09:29.580
Master Rimuru?

145
00:09:30.420 --> 00:09:32.007
M-Ms. Raphael?

146
00:09:32.090 --> 00:09:34.440
The problem hasn't been
resolved yet. you know!

147
00:09:34.890 --> 00:09:38.100
If you reflect after being scolded.
the problem will be solved.

148
00:09:43.100 --> 00:09:45.820
Y-You're joking. right...

149
00:09:53.360 --> 00:09:54.960
The existence of currency...

150
00:09:56.160 --> 00:09:58.910
...is indispensable to
the development of civilization.

151
00:10:00.580 --> 00:10:04.380
This marked the transition from an era
when grain was used as currency...

152
00:10:05.000 --> 00:10:08.750
...to one where it was gradually replaced
by coins made of gold and silver.

153
00:10:09.010 --> 00:10:13.610
and eventually to a paper-money economy
based on contracts and certificates.

154
00:10:15.800 --> 00:10:17.917
Even within the Western economic spheres.

155
00:10:18.000 --> 00:10:19.887
efforts were being made
through the council...

156
00:10:19.970 --> 00:10:24.850
...to transition to a paper-money economy
using each country's own currency.

157
00:10:26.080 --> 00:10:27.437
What's crucial is...

158
00:10:27.520 --> 00:10:31.470
...creating a system where exchange rates
fluctuate based on national strength.

159
00:10:32.020 --> 00:10:35.100
and ensuring that we are
the ones setting the rules.

160
00:10:36.550 --> 00:10:40.660
Lest we can't guarantee
an absolute domination.

161
00:10:46.560 --> 00:10:50.970
The value of each nation is determined
by the Council and the Five Elders.

162
00:10:52.550 --> 00:10:55.340
And the one calling the shots is.
of course...

163
00:10:56.540 --> 00:10:57.830
Me.

164
00:10:59.560 --> 00:11:02.980
I. will always rule.

165
00:11:10.180 --> 00:11:11.970
The Council of the West.

166
00:11:13.900 --> 00:11:15.777
or CoW. for short.

167
00:11:15.860 --> 00:11:17.897
KINGDOM OF INGRASSIA.
is a confederation comprising the nations

168
00:11:17.980 --> 00:11:19.840
COUNCIL OF THE WEST HEADQUARTERS
surrounding the Great Forest of Jura.

169
00:11:20.930 --> 00:11:27.290
The Council's goal was to benefit all
of humanity. regardless of a nation's size.

170
00:11:28.400 --> 00:11:31.547
Its topics ranged widely. with monster
countermeasures at top priority.

171
00:11:31.630 --> 00:11:36.010
followed by measures against droughts.
epidemics. and natural disasters.

172
00:11:37.890 --> 00:11:40.227
And the current topic of debate...

173
00:11:40.310 --> 00:11:44.810
...was whether or not to admit the monster
nation of Tempest into the council.

174
00:11:45.710 --> 00:11:49.107
Perchance. we can trust Tempest?

175
00:11:49.190 --> 00:11:50.437
So you say.

176
00:11:50.520 --> 00:11:54.107
but if we anger that Demon Lord.
won't he unleash the Storm Dragon on us?

177
00:11:54.190 --> 00:11:58.617
Don't sweat it. He's just a fox
borrowing the tiger's might.

178
00:11:58.700 --> 00:12:01.780
The Demon Lord himself
probably doesn't amount to much.

179
00:12:02.330 --> 00:12:06.957
Then how do you explain that
he managed to draw fighting Lady Hinata?!

180
00:12:07.040 --> 00:12:10.547
It's hard to say whether
that story is really true...

181
00:12:10.630 --> 00:12:11.707
He's right.

182
00:12:11.790 --> 00:12:14.337
Where did that information
come from again?

183
00:12:14.420 --> 00:12:17.820
They sure have the audacity to talk
about that right in front of me.

184
00:12:18.300 --> 00:12:22.260
I was invited here as someone
who knows the Demon Lord Rimuru.

185
00:12:22.790 --> 00:12:26.440
only to find out a bunch of incompetents
dragging things out like this...

186
00:12:28.100 --> 00:12:31.020
This is a far cry from the meetings
I had at Tempest...

187
00:12:32.320 --> 00:12:35.487
Well. I suppose Tempest's
is a special case.

188
00:12:35.570 --> 00:12:37.027
Listen.

189
00:12:37.110 --> 00:12:42.037
The Demon Lord Rimuru has declared
the Great Forest of Jura to be his territory!

190
00:12:42.120 --> 00:12:45.537
May each and every one of you
ponder the implications of this!

191
00:12:45.620 --> 00:12:49.207
Indeed. ever since
Tempest was established.

192
00:12:49.290 --> 00:12:53.087
the damage caused by monsters
in our homeland has been decreasing.

193
00:12:53.170 --> 00:12:56.837
Nonsense! You lot are being fooled
by the Demon Lord!

194
00:12:56.920 --> 00:12:58.927
We're dealing with
the king of the monsters!

195
00:12:59.010 --> 00:13:03.097
Well. unless you truly know what kind
of person the Demon Lord Rimuru is.

196
00:13:03.180 --> 00:13:07.350
there's no way you could say
whether he does good for people or not.

197
00:13:08.720 --> 00:13:12.940
But the real problem is the councilors
from the major countries.

198
00:13:13.650 --> 00:13:18.110
As for me. it would be convenient
if Tempest joined the Council. but...

199
00:13:18.930 --> 00:13:20.597
Ahem.

200
00:13:20.680 --> 00:13:22.947
We might as well accept it.

201
00:13:23.030 --> 00:13:27.247
If they say they want to join us.
we should welcome them.

202
00:13:27.330 --> 00:13:31.247
However. they must bring a souvenir.

203
00:13:31.330 --> 00:13:36.297
Sounds good. If we fight back.
we'll just end up like Falmuth.

204
00:13:36.380 --> 00:13:39.967
However. they should be
mindful of their position.

205
00:13:40.050 --> 00:13:44.177
Do they have any intention of abiding by
the international law we have established?

206
00:13:44.260 --> 00:13:46.727
It shouldn't be a problem.

207
00:13:46.810 --> 00:13:50.557
You've heard the rumors about
Duke Muese's downfall. haven't you?

208
00:13:50.640 --> 00:13:54.937
Who cares about
Demon Lord Rimuru's intentions?

209
00:13:55.020 --> 00:13:59.817
The only thing that matters is
whether he's useful or not. Period.

210
00:13:59.900 --> 00:14:01.697
That's right.

211
00:14:01.780 --> 00:14:04.327
Considering the developments in the East.

212
00:14:04.410 --> 00:14:08.327
there's surely no reason to refuse
the Demon Lord's forces as allies.

213
00:14:08.410 --> 00:14:10.287
The East. you say?!

214
00:14:10.370 --> 00:14:12.127
Do you mean the Eastern Empire?!

215
00:14:12.210 --> 00:14:15.000
Is that true. Lord Rostia?!

216
00:14:15.790 --> 00:14:19.677
As you all know. there are
movements in the military...

217
00:14:19.760 --> 00:14:25.300
...of the Nasca Namrium Ulmeria
United Eastern Empire.

218
00:14:25.690 --> 00:14:29.727
I heard they've been holding a lot
of military exercises lately.

219
00:14:29.810 --> 00:14:31.557
Are they now?!

220
00:14:31.640 --> 00:14:33.477
Why now. of all times?

221
00:14:33.560 --> 00:14:38.397
They're a military state that has devoured
countless countries voraciously!

222
00:14:38.480 --> 00:14:41.857
What will become of us
if war breaks out?!

223
00:14:41.940 --> 00:14:43.737
He's right!
- What'd we do if that happened?!

224
00:14:43.820 --> 00:14:45.287
Is war about to break out?!

225
00:14:45.370 --> 00:14:50.617
Calm down. It's not as if the Empire
is going to do anything right away.

226
00:14:50.700 --> 00:14:53.167
How can I possibly stay calm over this?!

227
00:14:53.250 --> 00:14:56.667
Now that the Kingdom of Falmuth
is gone. small nations like ours...

228
00:14:56.750 --> 00:14:59.527
...can't even establish defensive lines!

229
00:14:59.610 --> 00:15:04.180
That's why we should discuss
our countermeasures right here.

230
00:15:04.680 --> 00:15:05.637
However...

231
00:15:05.720 --> 00:15:08.977
Councilor Johann's point
is certainly valid.

232
00:15:09.060 --> 00:15:11.720
Please try to compose yourself. everyone.

233
00:15:12.120 --> 00:15:14.687
If we just throw our opinions
at each other without restraint.

234
00:15:14.770 --> 00:15:16.980
then there is no point
in having a council.

235
00:15:17.480 --> 00:15:20.137
Thank you. Councilor Gaban.

236
00:15:20.220 --> 00:15:21.317
It's nothing.

237
00:15:21.400 --> 00:15:25.157
I just don't think the Empire
would take action anytime soon.

238
00:15:25.240 --> 00:15:28.537
The reason the Empire has never
attacked us so far...

239
00:15:28.620 --> 00:15:32.617
...is because that Storm Dragon
was in the Great Forest of Jura.

240
00:15:32.700 --> 00:15:36.167
And now it has been revived.

241
00:15:36.250 --> 00:15:40.500
Are you really considering
relying on that evil dragon?

242
00:15:41.000 --> 00:15:42.757
Perhaps you all have forgotten.

243
00:15:42.840 --> 00:15:47.807
The Storm Dragon is now under
the control of the Demon Lord Rimuru.

244
00:15:47.890 --> 00:15:53.437
And I believe he wishes
to join the Council. does he not?

245
00:15:53.520 --> 00:15:54.157
Ridiculous!

246
00:15:54.240 --> 00:15:55.267
That Storm Dragon?!

247
00:15:55.350 --> 00:15:56.520
There's no way...

248
00:15:57.190 --> 00:16:01.107
As Councilor Gaban said.
in the face of the Eastern threat.

249
00:16:01.190 --> 00:16:04.687
this is no time for us to be
squabbling over our differences.

250
00:16:04.770 --> 00:16:08.257
If the Demon Lord Rimuru
were to join the council.

251
00:16:08.340 --> 00:16:12.247
his military might would surely
be of great assistance to us!

252
00:16:12.330 --> 00:16:17.497
Indeed. We must unite the West.
first and foremost.

253
00:16:17.580 --> 00:16:19.747
That goes without saying.

254
00:16:19.830 --> 00:16:22.507
I support bringing Tempest in!

255
00:16:22.590 --> 00:16:23.347
Me too!

256
00:16:23.430 --> 00:16:24.507
That's a sensible choice.

257
00:16:24.590 --> 00:16:26.840
Let's welcome Tempest to the Council!

258
00:16:28.880 --> 00:16:30.340
Order in the court. please.

259
00:16:30.930 --> 00:16:37.237
Now. let us vote on whether to approve
Tempest's joining the Council or not.

260
00:16:37.320 --> 00:16:39.850
Those in favor. please stand up.

261
00:16:43.360 --> 00:16:45.737
By a majority vote.

262
00:16:45.820 --> 00:16:51.370
the Jura Tempest Federation
shall be recognized as our ally.

263
00:16:51.920 --> 00:16:56.537
After sending an invitation to
the Jura Tempest Federation. the country itself.

264
00:16:56.620 --> 00:16:59.787
and confirming the will
of the Demon Lord Rimuru.

265
00:16:59.870 --> 00:17:02.880
the next meeting shall be convened.

266
00:17:03.340 --> 00:17:04.380
That is all.

267
00:17:11.290 --> 00:17:16.150
In the end. they only called me
because they're afraid of Rimuru.

268
00:17:16.680 --> 00:17:19.016
Honestly. they should have
just asked me to make sure

269
00:17:19.099 --> 00:17:21.516
the Demon Lord Rimuru
doesn't go on a rampage.

270
00:17:21.599 --> 00:17:26.150
Using the Empire as a mere pretext.
What a farce.

271
00:17:28.130 --> 00:17:31.050
I really don't want anything
more to do with the nobles.

272
00:17:31.960 --> 00:17:32.980
Miss Hinata.

273
00:17:36.490 --> 00:17:37.577
Ugh...

274
00:17:37.660 --> 00:17:39.710
The Firstborn Prince of Engrassia...

275
00:17:40.500 --> 00:17:43.650
Of all the nobles. I just had to
meet the most troublesome one.

276
00:17:44.750 --> 00:17:46.800
Do you need something from me?

277
00:17:47.340 --> 00:17:52.850
Would you mind sparing me
a moment of your time?

278
00:17:57.130 --> 00:17:59.810
So. what exactly do you wish to discuss?

279
00:18:00.620 --> 00:18:04.377
Actually. I have a request for you.

280
00:18:04.460 --> 00:18:09.820
I'm planning to test Demon Lord Rimuru
at the next meeting.

281
00:18:12.070 --> 00:18:14.987
The Demon Lord may
possess immense power.

282
00:18:15.070 --> 00:18:19.700
but as a member of the Council.
he must fulfill his obligations accordingly.

283
00:18:20.660 --> 00:18:26.570
Besides. we need to find out how much
he'll listen to our side of the story.

284
00:18:28.300 --> 00:18:29.497
Is that so?

285
00:18:29.580 --> 00:18:31.177
And...

286
00:18:31.260 --> 00:18:33.760
...that's where you come in!

287
00:18:34.910 --> 00:18:36.767
Since he's the Demon Lord.

288
00:18:36.850 --> 00:18:39.970
it would be a disaster
if he were to go on a rampage.

289
00:18:40.500 --> 00:18:45.270
I'd like to ask you to guard me.

290
00:18:47.560 --> 00:18:49.277
Why me?

291
00:18:49.360 --> 00:18:51.570
Huh? Why. you say...

292
00:18:52.730 --> 00:18:56.817
T-That's because
I recognize your strength!

293
00:18:56.900 --> 00:18:59.327
As the strongest Commander
of the Holy Knights in history.

294
00:18:59.410 --> 00:19:03.937
I honor your strength as the Right Hand
of God and the Master Rooks!

295
00:19:04.020 --> 00:19:07.377
There is no one in the Western
nations who can match you.

296
00:19:07.460 --> 00:19:10.677
There are even rumors that you fought
the Demon Lord Rimuru to a draw!

297
00:19:10.760 --> 00:19:12.967
If you're willing to cooperate.

298
00:19:13.050 --> 00:19:17.050
we can safely uncover the true
nature of the Demon Lord Rimuru!

299
00:19:18.010 --> 00:19:23.320
I wonder if this guy even realizes
what he's saying to me.

300
00:19:24.280 --> 00:19:26.560
I suggest you refrain from doing that.

301
00:19:27.900 --> 00:19:29.980
He is really strong.

302
00:19:30.380 --> 00:19:34.450
There's no guarantee I could win
against him if we fight again.

303
00:19:35.540 --> 00:19:38.157
After all. the rumor
that we fought to a draw...

304
00:19:38.240 --> 00:19:40.540
...was deliberately spread
in the first place.

305
00:19:43.230 --> 00:19:47.247
Lady Hinata. you don't have to
act all demure just because...

306
00:19:47.330 --> 00:19:50.207
...you're in front of Lord Elric.

307
00:19:50.290 --> 00:19:54.117
Although I wouldn't blame you
for falling for his charming face.

308
00:19:54.200 --> 00:19:55.597
I have to refuse.

309
00:19:55.680 --> 00:19:56.260
Huh?!

310
00:19:57.610 --> 00:20:02.117
The Western Holy Church
and the Holy Empire of Lubelius...

311
00:20:02.200 --> 00:20:05.767
...have signed a non-aggression pact
with Tempest.

312
00:20:05.850 --> 00:20:08.947
Also. a word of advice. if I may.

313
00:20:09.030 --> 00:20:11.777
I suggest you refrain from angering
the Demon Lord Rimuru.

314
00:20:11.860 --> 00:20:13.247
What did you say?!

315
00:20:13.330 --> 00:20:15.440
Y-You dare give me orders?!

316
00:20:18.060 --> 00:20:23.487
Also. isn't it mandatory that a formal request
should be handed in properly?

317
00:20:23.570 --> 00:20:25.330
I was just...

318
00:20:25.890 --> 00:20:27.330
Excuse me.

319
00:20:31.860 --> 00:20:33.710
You'll regret this. Miss Hinata!

320
00:20:35.760 --> 00:20:40.290
Unfortunately for you.
I trust Demon Lord Rimuru.

321
00:20:50.770 --> 00:20:55.107
A flimsy plan that just tries to take
advantage of whatever happens...

322
00:20:55.190 --> 00:20:56.590
...is bound to be a failure.

323
00:20:57.770 --> 00:20:58.770
But...

324
00:21:00.740 --> 00:21:03.390
What if this conversation
and that meeting earlier...

325
00:21:03.960 --> 00:21:07.250
...were both something planned
from the start by someone...

326
00:21:11.780 --> 00:21:14.610
I guess that's a tad far-fetched. huh?

327
00:21:19.630 --> 00:21:22.550
Shall we head out now.
Master Rimuru?

328
00:21:23.430 --> 00:21:24.890
Yeah. you're right!

329
00:21:27.730 --> 00:21:28.897
Master Rimuru!

330
00:21:28.980 --> 00:21:30.067
Shion?

331
00:21:30.150 --> 00:21:31.227
Ah!

332
00:21:31.310 --> 00:21:33.977
Why do I have to stay behind?

333
00:21:34.060 --> 00:21:37.907
It's not fair that you're taking
Lady Shuna and the others with you!

334
00:21:37.990 --> 00:21:40.950
Oh. about that. you see...

335
00:21:44.930 --> 00:21:45.967
Shion!

336
00:21:46.050 --> 00:21:48.897
You're not just here to sit around!

337
00:21:48.980 --> 00:21:52.170
Many of Tempest's top executives
are away right now.

338
00:21:52.560 --> 00:21:54.957
That means you.
as the First Secretary.

339
00:21:55.040 --> 00:21:57.257
are the only one
who can protect this place!

340
00:21:57.340 --> 00:21:58.420
Oh!

341
00:21:59.270 --> 00:22:00.790
Can you do it?

342
00:22:01.910 --> 00:22:02.930
Sir!

343
00:22:05.170 --> 00:22:10.680
I'm still a little worried about taking her
to a big city with so many humans.

344
00:22:14.300 --> 00:22:16.440
All right. that's everyone.

345
00:22:17.610 --> 00:22:19.710
I'm counting on you
while I'm away. Shion.

346
00:22:19.890 --> 00:22:20.867
Sir!

347
00:22:20.950 --> 00:22:22.530
Have a safe trip!

348
00:22:23.940 --> 00:22:25.160
Shall we go?

349
00:22:33.500 --> 00:22:35.530
Let's go to the Council!

350
00:24:05.880 --> 00:24:08.620
Next time: The First Step.

351
